### Sample HTTP requests for TranslateHub API

# 1. Create a translation task (upload file, specify source/target language)
POST http://localhost:8080/tasks
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="dialogue.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

Hello, how are you?
This is a test.
--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="user"

alice
--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="source_lang"

en
--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="target_lang"

jp
--boundary--

### 2. List all translation tasks
GET http://localhost:8080/tasks

### 3. Submit a translation change for a dialogue line
POST http://localhost:8080/changes
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

task_id=1&dialogue_id=1&user=bob&new_trans=こんにちは、お元気ですか？

### 4. Review (approve) a submitted change (by task creator)
POST http://localhost:8080/review
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

task_id=1&change_id=1&user=alice&status=approved

### 5. Review (reject) a submitted change (by task creator)
POST http://localhost:8080/review
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

task_id=1&change_id=1&user=alice&status=rejected
